July 28, 2017 2:12 PM ET
Professional Services

Company Overview of Dykema Gossett PLLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Rex E. Schlaybaugh Jr., J.D.Chairman Emeritus and Member, Dykema Gossett PLLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships68--
Background

		Mr. Rex E. Schlaybaugh, Jr., also known as Bill, J.D., served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Dykema Gossett PLLC from 2002 to December, 2011. Mr. Schlaybaugh represents issuers, underwriters and equity investors in a range of financing transactions, joint ventures and strategic partnerships, including private and public offerings of securities, secured and unsecured senior, mezzanine and subordinated debt facilities. Mr. Schlaybaugh has experience and ... judgment in guiding client’s legal affairs in broad cross-section of industries including automotive, energy and financial services. He provides general corporate and securities counsel to many of its corporate clients and advises several Boards of Directors on various corporate issues. Mr. Schlaybaugh served as Secretary of Oxford Automotive Inc since 1995. He retired from Oxford Automotive Inc. on October 6, 2003. He serves as Chair Emeritus at Dykema Gossett PLLC. He has over 35 years of operations management experience in manufacturing on a global basis. He serves as Chairman of SIL Realisations 2013 Limited. Mr. Schlaybaugh served as Vice Chairman of Oxford Automotive Inc since May 1997. He served as Vice Chairman of The Oxford Investment Group, Inc. since May 1997. Mr. Schlaybaugh serves on a number of Boards of Directors including The Manufacturers Life Insurance Company, The Bank of Bloomfield Hills and the Michigan State Chamber of Commerce. He has been an Independent Director of Syntel, Inc. since October 10, 2016. He has been a Director of Dykema Gossett PLLC since 1985. He also serves as a Member of the Board of Trustees of Oakland University. Mr. Schlaybaugh is a Member of the Board of Directors of Detroit Economic Growth Corporation, a Member of the Board of Directors of the Detroit Economic Club and the Metropolitan Affairs Coalition. He serves on a number of Boards of Directors of various business entities, including The John Hancock Life Insurance Company and Sealine International Ltd. Mr. Schlaybaugh is a Member of the Dean's Advisory Board of the University of Detroit Mercy School of Law. He served as Director of Oxford Automotive Inc since 1995. He served as Director of Oxford Investment Group. He is the immediate past Chairman of the Michigan Chamber of Commerce and past Chairman and Member of the Board of Trustees of Oakland University. He is also past Chairman of the Detroit Legal Aid and Defender Association's Legal Legacy Campaign. He was a recognized in The Best Lawyers in America for Corporate Law, Mergers and Acquisitions Law and Securities/Capital Markets Law from 2007 till present. He was named a Michigan Leading Lawyer in the areas of Corporate Finance, Mergers and Acquisitions and Publicly Held Corporations Law by the Leading Lawyers Network in 2014-2016. He was named a Michigan Leader in the Law, 2010 and recognized in Michigan Super Lawyers for Securities & Corporate Finance and Mergers & Acquisitions from 2008-2015. He was named a Top Lawyer by dbusiness Magazine for Corporate Law, Mergers and Acquisitions Law, Securities/Capital Markets Law, 2010-2011, 2013 and 2015-2016. Mr. Schlaybaugh is a recipient of an AV Preeminent Rating by Martindale-Hubbell. Mr. Schlaybaugh is a frequent speaker on merger and acquisition matters and on corporate governance issues facing Boards of Directors. Mr. Schlaybaugh is a member of the Business Law Section of the State Bar of Michigan since 1974 and the American Bar Association. Mr. Schlaybaugh has a B.A. in Economics from Albion College and a J.D. from the University of Detroit School of Law.Read Full Background




